[This quarantine action is in response to the new US CDC rules for Congo DR and Guinea travelers.

"The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) issued new public health requirements for US visitors who have recently been in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) or Guinea because of concerns about Ebola that take effect 4 Mar 2021, to address Ebola concerns, the agency said.

"Travelers who have been in the 2 central African countries within the past 21 days must fly to New York-JFK, Chicago, Atlanta, Washington Dulles, Newark or Los Angeles. The CDC will require airlines to collect and transmit passenger information electronically to the agency for public health follow-up for all passengers who have been in the 2 countries who are boarding a flight to the United States."
(From https://www.hindustantimes.com/lifestyle/travel/new-us-cdc-rules-for-drc-guinea-travelers-take-effect-Thursday-101614743175153.html 3 Mar 2021).

The CDC order can be seen at https://www.cdc.gov/quarantine/order-contact-information-ebola.html.
