[2] Congo DR: last Ebola patient
Date: Wed 23 Mar 2021
Source: CGTN Africa (edited)]
https://africa.cgtn.com/2021/03/23/dr-congo-releases-last-known-ebola-patients-from-north-kivu-treatment-centers/


The Democratic Republic of Congo released its last confirmed Ebola patients from the treatment centers on Monday [22 Mar 2021], health authorities said.

The country has begun a 42-day countdown to declaring DR Congo free of the virus.

The release of 6 patients on Monday [22 Mar 2021] from the treatment centers in the North Kivu region could mark the end of a month-long resurgence of the 2018-20 epidemic which killed more than 2200 people before it was initially declared over in June 2020.

The World Health Organization confirmed that the last patient was discharged from a treatment center in Katwa yesterday [22 Mar 2021].

